<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="gr-crust" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Graham Pie Crust</title>

  <p>
    Ingredients:
  </p>
  <tabular>
    <row>
      <cell>10-11 full sheet graham crackers</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>5-6 Tablespoons unsalted butter, melted</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>1/4-1/3 cup sugar</cell>
    </row>
  </tabular>

  <p>Instructions
    <ol>
      <li>
        <p>
          Use a food processor or blender to grind up graham crackers. Or crush them in a zipped top bag with a rolling pin.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Mix the graham cracker crumbs, melted butter, and sugar together with a rubber spatula in a medium bowl until combined. The mixture will be thick, coarse, and sandy.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Press the mixture into the bottom of the greased dish or pan and slightly up the sides.  Make sure it is tight and compact. Use the bottom of a flat measuring cup.  The crust will be thick.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          For a baked dessert, pre-bake for 10 minutes at <m>300^\circ</m>F or 7-8 minutes at <m>350^\circ</m>F. For a no-bake dessert, chill the crust for 2 hours before using.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </p>

  <p>
    Notes:
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p>
          For the ingredients, use the lower measurements for a smaller pie and the higher measurements for a larger pie.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          This crust is used in <alert>Chocolate Silk Pie</alert>.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </p>
</section>